meanings.definition: To move more quickly or forcefully than someone or something else.
meanings.sent1: The cheetah outmoved the other animals in the race.
meanings.sent2: The car outmoved the bicycle on the road.
meanings.sent3: The squirrel outmoved the turtle in the race to the tree.
meanings.sent4: The wind outmoved the clouds across the sky.
meanings.sent5: The river outmoved the rocks in its path.

meanings.definition: To be emotionally affected or influenced by something.
meanings.sent1: She was outmoved by the touching story.
meanings.sent2: He outmoved his friends with his heartfelt speech.
meanings.sent3: The puppy outmoved everyone with its adorable antics.
meanings.sent4: The music outmoved her to tears.
meanings.sent5: The movie outmoved the audience with its powerful message.
